-- Justices agree to hear Daimler human rights case
-- 
-- Mon Apr 22, 2013 9:49am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/22/us-usa-court-rights-idUSBRE93L0L220130422

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The Supreme Court on Monday agreed to hear a Daimler AG ( DAIGn.DE ) appeal concerning human rights allegations against the company. 
 The San Francisco-based 9th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals had ruled in favor of plaintiffs in allowing claims to proceed in federal court. (Reporting by Lawrence Hurley; Editing by  Howard Goller  and Gerald E. McCormick)